						<summary>

						<p>Fragment of a slab lying near the well in fron of the Śiva temple to the north of the Aṅkāḷamma temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1646, Śōbhakṛit, Śrāvaṇa śu. 7, Monday.</hi> The details of the date are wrong.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. It seems to state that upto the date specified certain renovations (details lost) were carried out near the shrines of Vīrēśvara and Siddhanāthadēva of Vēlpunūru.</p>						

						</summary>
